text.section:
The articles of incorporation shall include:
the purpose for which the society is being formed and the manner in which its corporate powers are to be exercised;
the name of the society;
the name, address, and state of residence of each incorporator; and
the name, address, residence, and official title of each officer, trustee, director, and any other individual who will have general control of the management of the affairs and funds of the society for the first year and until the first election.
